{
  "video_id": "0knxW76bDuI",
  "title": "Credited As: ConLangers (How to Create a Language)",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3165.0,
      "end_time": 6165.0,
      "text": "Peterson: the biggest misconception about language creation"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 6165.0,
      "end_time": 9297.0,
      "text": "Is that it's just a matter of taking an english dictionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9297.0,
      "end_time": 10693.0,
      "text": "and making up forms for it."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10693.0,
      "end_time": 12363.0,
      "text": "You can do that, but what you're doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12363.0,
      "end_time": 13759.0,
      "text": "Is essentially just creating"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13759.0,
      "end_time": 15726.0,
      "text": "a really bizarre way of speaking English."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 15726.0,
      "end_time": 17627.0,
      "text": "Frommer: With finite means,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 17627.0,
      "end_time": 20296.0,
      "text": "we can create an infinite number of messages."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20297.0,
      "end_time": 22165.0,
      "text": "Okrand: It's not bringing to life something that i've created."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 23495.0,
      "end_time": 25330.0,
      "text": "It's bringing to better life something that somebody else has created."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28660.0,
      "end_time": 30363.0,
      "text": "Peterson: \"Conlang\" means a constructed language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30363.0,
      "end_time": 31363.0,
      "text": "and that's what we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 31363.0,
      "end_time": 32726.0,
      "text": "The first thing i do"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 32726.0,
      "end_time": 34561.0,
      "text": "when i'm creating a new language for a new project"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 34561.0,
      "end_time": 36759.0,
      "text": "is I sit down with either the show runner, or the director if it's a film, and the producers."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 39132.0,
      "end_time": 42396.0,
      "text": "I grill them about who is speaking this language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 42396.0,
      "end_time": 44594.0,
      "text": "Who are the people, where are they from."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 44594.0,
      "end_time": 47264.0,
      "text": "I came to work on \"Thor: The Dark World\""
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 47264.0,
      "end_time": 49231.0,
      "text": "because the director, Alan Taylor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 49231.0,
      "end_time": 51759.0,
      "text": "had worked with me on HBO's \"Game of Thrones.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 51759.0,
      "end_time": 54363.0,
      "text": "what they wanted was a language for the dark elves --"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 54363.0,
      "end_time": 57330.0,
      "text": "kind of one of the bad guys in the Thor universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 57330.0,
      "end_time": 59198.0,
      "text": "Malekith: [speaking Shivaaisith]"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 63165.0,
      "end_time": 66164.0,
      "text": "Frommer: The world that James Cameron created on Pandora"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 66165.0,
      "end_time": 68198.0,
      "text": "is so incredibly detailed."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 68198.0,
      "end_time": 70363.0,
      "text": "it's up to me as a language creator"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 70363.0,
      "end_time": 73462.0,
      "text": "to understand that world to the best of my ability."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 73462.0,
      "end_time": 77264.0,
      "text": "And then to create a language which would be appropriate for people living in that environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 79330.0,
      "end_time": 82429.0,
      "text": "Okrand: In making up Klingon, i tried very, very hard"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 82429.0,
      "end_time": 85165.0,
      "text": "to not make it resemble anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 85165.0,
      "end_time": 87231.0,
      "text": "Because klingons, at the time --"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 87231.0,
      "end_time": 90000.0,
      "text": "all we knew about them is they're mean, horrible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 90000.0,
      "end_time": 91000.0,
      "text": "awful people."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 91000.0,
      "end_time": 92429.0,
      "text": "So, i didn't want somebody"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 92429.0,
      "end_time": 94231.0,
      "text": "To come up to me afterwards and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 94231.0,
      "end_time": 97297.0,
      "text": "\"How come you made the Klingon language like my language?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 97297.0,
      "end_time": 99297.0,
      "text": "What's that saying about me? That's an insult.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 99297.0,
      "end_time": 103000.0,
      "text": "Kruge: [speaking Klingon]"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 104198.0,
      "end_time": 105494.0,
      "text": "Peterson: The first discussion that we have"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 105495.0,
      "end_time": 107330.0,
      "text": "is for the sound of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 107330.0,
      "end_time": 109264.0,
      "text": "I created a language called Shivaaisith,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 109264.0,
      "end_time": 110461.0,
      "text": "which, when you hear it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 110462.0,
      "end_time": 112429.0,
      "text": "it's reminiscent of the Finnish language."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 112429.0,
      "end_time": 114198.0,
      "text": "They have a bunch of top-heavy words"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 114198.0,
      "end_time": 116527.0,
      "text": "where there's nice prominence right at the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 121462.0,
      "end_time": 123495.0,
      "text": "Frommer: In terms of the sound system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 123495.0,
      "end_time": 125396.0,
      "text": "I didn't start from absolute zero."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 125396.0,
      "end_time": 126759.0,
      "text": "James Cameron had, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 126759.0,
      "end_time": 129980.0,
      "text": "come up with a few words on his own."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 129979.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131429.0,
      "text": "These were mainly names of characters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 131429.0,
      "end_time": 133561.0,
      "text": "names of places on Pandora."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 133561.0,
      "end_time": 135726.0,
      "text": "Sully: [speaking Na'VI]"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 144000.0,
      "end_time": 145627.0,
      "text": "Frommer: In the Na'Vi sound system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 145627.0,
      "end_time": 147363.0,
      "text": "there are sounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 147363.0,
      "end_time": 149198.0,
      "text": "Which you can find in Polynesian languages."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 149198.0,
      "end_time": 151561.0,
      "text": "But also sounds which are not found in those languages --"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 151561.0,
      "end_time": 155000.0,
      "text": "the -- the best known ones are called ejectives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 155000.0,
      "end_time": 156726.0,
      "text": "which are sort of popping sounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 156726.0,
      "end_time": 159363.0,
      "text": "they sound like \"[pops lips] ah\" or \"[clicks] eh\""
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 159363.0,
      "end_time": 161000.0,
      "text": "or \"[clicks] ooh.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 161000.0,
      "end_time": 162759.0,
      "text": "Okrand: for Klingon, the script said explicitly"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 162759.0,
      "end_time": 164231.0,
      "text": "that the language was guttural."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 164231.0,
      "end_time": 165462.0,
      "text": "Well, guttural can mean a lot of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 165462.0,
      "end_time": 166594.0,
      "text": "but the way i interpreted it"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 166594.0,
      "end_time": 168231.0,
      "text": "is \"hch\" kinds of sounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 168231.0,
      "end_time": 170594.0,
      "text": "I've had two kind of basic things in mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 170594.0,
      "end_time": 175660.0,
      "text": "One was it had to sound weird and alien and not like anything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 175660.0,
      "end_time": 179231.0,
      "text": "and two, the actors had to be able to learn it and say it."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 179231.0,
      "end_time": 181297.0,
      "text": "So, the thing was pronounceable and learnable."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 182528.0,
      "end_time": 185495.0,
      "text": "Which means success. That's my favorite word."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 185495.0,
      "end_time": 187990.0,
      "text": "Peterson: When you actually get into it"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 187990.0,
      "end_time": 188363.0,
      "text": "and start creating a language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 188363.0,
      "end_time": 189528.0,
      "text": "the first thing that you have to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 189528.0,
      "end_time": 191165.0,
      "text": "is create the grammatical system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 191165.0,
      "end_time": 193197.0,
      "text": "and that thing pretty much has to be complete."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 193198.0,
      "end_time": 195132.0,
      "text": "Frommer: the Na'Vi parts of speech"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 195132.0,
      "end_time": 198990.0,
      "text": "are not unlike parts of speech in more familiar languages."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 198990.0,
      "end_time": 199692.0,
      "text": "so, we have nouns, we have verbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 199693.0,
      "end_time": 201594.0,
      "text": "we have adjectives, we have adverbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 209990.0,
      "end_time": 210494.0,
      "text": "And this means,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 210495.0,
      "end_time": 214363.0,
      "text": "\"Eytukan gave Neythiri this beautiful necklace.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 214363.0,
      "end_time": 215462.0,
      "text": "Okrand: For klingon, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 215462.0,
      "end_time": 217131.0,
      "text": "there was already some Klingon."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 217132.0,
      "end_time": 219330.0,
      "text": "There was Klingon in \"star trek: the motion picture.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 219330.0,
      "end_time": 222363.0,
      "text": "So I kind of imposed a grammatical structure on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 222363.0,
      "end_time": 225165.0,
      "text": "For example, a three-syllable phrase --"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 225165.0,
      "end_time": 226594.0,
      "text": "[speaking Klingon]"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 228132.0,
      "end_time": 229462.0,
      "text": "Is that one word or two words or three words?"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 229462.0,
      "end_time": 231726.0,
      "text": "So, I just arbitrarily decided."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 231726.0,
      "end_time": 234231.0,
      "text": "\"Cha\" was one word. \"Yighus\" is another word."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 234231.0,
      "end_time": 237231.0,
      "text": "It's supposed to be an alien language unlike anything else."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 237231.0,
      "end_time": 239759.0,
      "text": "The three basic elements of a sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 239759.0,
      "end_time": 241692.0,
      "text": "are the subject, the verb, and the object."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 241693.0,
      "end_time": 243726.0,
      "text": "There are six possible combinations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 243726.0,
      "end_time": 247264.0,
      "text": "and the least common is when the object comes first."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 247264.0,
      "end_time": 248726.0,
      "text": "So, that's the one I chose for Klingon."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 250462.0,
      "end_time": 252462.0,
      "text": "Peterson: when I actually translate a line,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 252462.0,
      "end_time": 254759.0,
      "text": "What I do is there's the English line up top,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 254759.0,
      "end_time": 256428.0,
      "text": "then there's the translated line,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 256428.0,
      "end_time": 258462.0,
      "text": "then there's a line below that shows them"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 258462.0,
      "end_time": 260330.0,
      "text": "where the emphasis is supposed to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 260329.99999999997,
      "end_time": 262990.0,
      "text": "So, it breaks up every word by syllables,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 262990.0,
      "end_time": 263396.0,
      "text": "and the one that's supposed to get the big emphasis"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 263396.0,
      "end_time": 265132.0,
      "text": "is in all caps."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 265132.0,
      "end_time": 267330.0,
      "text": "Frommer: In addition to that, I made little recordings."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 267330.0,
      "end_time": 274296.0,
      "text": "[speaking Na'Vi]"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 274297.0,
      "end_time": 275759.0,
      "text": "Okrand: Most of the time, I'm on the set."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 275759.0,
      "end_time": 278561.0,
      "text": "And will work with the actors prior to any take,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 278561.0,
      "end_time": 280462.0,
      "text": "sometimes a day before, even a week before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 280462.0,
      "end_time": 282231.0,
      "text": "sometimes minutes before."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 282231.0,
      "end_time": 284165.0,
      "text": "But especially in the early days of Klingon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 284165.0,
      "end_time": 285759.0,
      "text": "since no one had heard the language before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 285759.0,
      "end_time": 289660.0,
      "text": "if the actor made a mistake and said \"toe\" instead of \"too,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 289660.0,
      "end_time": 291131.0,
      "text": "I'd say, \"that's fine,\" and make myself a note."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 291132.0,
      "end_time": 292561.0,
      "text": "\"Okay, next time that word comes up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 292561.0,
      "end_time": 294626.0,
      "text": "He's gonna say 'toe' and not 'too.'\""
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 294627.0,
      "end_time": 297429.0,
      "text": "So, the language changes as a result of movie making."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 297429.0,
      "end_time": 300990.0,
      "text": "Man: [speaking Klingon ]"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 300990.0,
      "end_time": 302164.0,
      "text": "Peterson: I think one of the great things about creating a language"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 302165.0,
      "end_time": 304660.0,
      "text": "is that you get a level of fan interaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 304660.0,
      "end_time": 307990.0,
      "text": "That you never would have expected."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 307990.0,
      "end_time": 310330.0,
      "text": "Like, for example, with the Na'Vi language in \"Avatar,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 310330.0,
      "end_time": 312429.0,
      "text": "There are people that speak it fluently now."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 312429.0,
      "end_time": 314395.0,
      "text": "frommer: I'm continually getting suggestions from the Na'Vi community for new vocabulary."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 317330.0,
      "end_time": 319264.0,
      "text": "I'm still the gatekeeper."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 319264.0,
      "end_time": 321396.0,
      "text": "I'm still the only one who can say, \"This is fantastic. This is in the language.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 323264.0,
      "end_time": 326495.0,
      "text": "But this collaborative process, it's been very satisfying to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 326495.0,
      "end_time": 328660.0,
      "text": "Okrand: Klingon continues to grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 328660.0,
      "end_time": 329527.0,
      "text": "These days, I mean, every once in a while, if there's a new film or a TV show --"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 331132.0,
      "end_time": 332561.0,
      "text": "the last J.J. Abrams \"Star Trek\" movie"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 332561.0,
      "end_time": 335231.0,
      "text": "had Klingon in it and had a lot of new vocabulary."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 335231.0,
      "end_time": 338363.0,
      "text": "There's Klingon speakers all over the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 338363.0,
      "end_time": 339759.0,
      "text": "Some of them are beginners."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 339759.0,
      "end_time": 342000.0,
      "text": "Some of them are absolutely fluent."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 342000.0,
      "end_time": 343759.0,
      "text": "I have people all over the world who are mad at me"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 343759.0,
      "end_time": 346000.0,
      "text": "because I'm not producing vocabulary quickly enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 346000.0,
      "end_time": 348264.0,
      "text": "It's part of linguistics curricula."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 348264.0,
      "end_time": 350660.0,
      "text": "I never thought that anything like that would happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 350660.0,
      "end_time": 352462.0,
      "text": "Peterson: when you speak a language"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 352462.0,
      "end_time": 354330.0,
      "text": "and you learn it to fluency, that becomes a part of you."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 354330.0,
      "end_time": 356000.0,
      "text": "And so, that, I always thought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 356000.0,
      "end_time": 358990.0,
      "text": "was just the most fascinating thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 358990.0,
      "end_time": 359659.0,
      "text": "the most awesome thing about adding a created language to a production"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 361495.0,
      "end_time": 364660.0,
      "text": "because you can get that constant, deep level of interaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 365330.0,
      "end_time": 367264.0,
      "text": "that you can't with anything else."
    }
  ]
}